text: When i was on vacation in coastal Japan i witnessed many dolphins being horrifically slaughtered by Japanese fishermen for meat. They would first harpoon the dolphins then pull them on their boats and use a machete to hack them up while they were still alive. It was so horrible because the fishermen had no compassion and were in no hurry to put the dolphins out of their misery, they smoked and talked in-between strikes of their machetes. The desperate squeaks of pain these animals made will stay with me forever. One of the fisher-men let me shoot a harpoon at a dolphin and i also got to chop it up so i am looking forward to watching this film.
